headline: 3 Reasons to Sell WM and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since June 2024, Waste Management has been in a holding pattern, posting a small loss of 3.2% while floating around $205.38. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 10.4% gain during that period.
